Wingerworth has one parade of shops at Edinburgh Court consisting of these types of shops:
{Supermarket Post Office/Newsagent {Bakers Butchers { Greengrocers Hairdressers}
When we went to the shops we questionned the customers and the shop keepers. We found that people only used these 'local' shops if they found it difficult to get into Chesterfield to the larger and cheaper shops, eg. if they had a small baby, or if they didn't have a car. Some people did all their main food and household shopping in bulk once a month, so they just came to Edinburgh Court twice a week for perishable goods.
